<h2>What to Do After You Have the Output</h2>
<p>Running a prompt is step one. Here is how to turn raw ChatGPT output into published marketing assets.</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Edit for your voice.</strong> AI output is a first draft. Adjust tone, remove filler, and add brand-specific language.</li>
<li><strong>Add real data.</strong> Replace placeholder statistics with verified numbers from your analytics or published research.</li>
<li><strong>Check for accuracy.</strong> ChatGPT can generate plausible-sounding but incorrect claims. Verify every fact and link.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/blog/humanize-ai-content/">Humanize the content</a>.</strong> Remove patterns that signal AI writing. Vary sentence lengths. Add personal experience.</li>
<li><strong>Optimize for SEO.</strong> Run the output through your <a href="/blog/on-page-seo-guide/">on-page checklist</a>. Verify keyword placement, headers, and meta tags.</li>
<li><strong>Publish consistently.</strong> A single prompt is a tactic. A <a href="/blog/content-marketing-strategy/">content strategy</a> with 30+ posts per month is a growth engine.</li>
</ol>
